From: stopless-java-gc <noreply@anthropic.com>
Subject: [PATCH 0004/N] flags-cflags.m4: set _ALLBSD_SOURCE for JVM on bsd target

OpenJDK 17u sets `CFLAGS_OS_DEF_JDK="-D_ALLBSD_SOURCE"` for the
OPENJDK_TARGET_OS=bsd path but leaves `CFLAGS_OS_DEF_JVM` empty.
HotSpot's `globalDefinitions_gcc.hpp` guards its primitive-type
typedefs with `#if !defined(LINUX) && !defined(_ALLBSD_SOURCE)`,
so without `-D_ALLBSD_SOURCE` on JVM compiles those typedefs
collide with system headers' definitions (especially on CHERI where
intptr_t is `__intcap`, not `int`).

Mirror the macosx branch: define `_ALLBSD_SOURCE` for JVM too, and
add `_GNU_SOURCE` for parity with the Linux JVM path.

Refs: docs/05_zgc_cheri_collision_report.md §5

--- a/make/autoconf/flags-cflags.m4
+++ b/make/autoconf/flags-cflags.m4
@@ -427,6 +427,7 @@ AC_DEFUN([FLAGS_SETUP_CFLAGS_HELPER],
   elif test "x$OPENJDK_TARGET_OS" = xaix; then
     CFLAGS_OS_DEF_JVM="-DAIX"
   elif test "x$OPENJDK_TARGET_OS" = xbsd; then
+    CFLAGS_OS_DEF_JVM="-D_ALLBSD_SOURCE -D_GNU_SOURCE"
     CFLAGS_OS_DEF_JDK="-D_ALLBSD_SOURCE"
   elif test "x$OPENJDK_TARGET_OS" = xwindows; then
     CFLAGS_OS_DEF_JVM="-D_WINDOWS -DWIN32 -D_JNI_IMPLEMENTATION_"
